WEBVTT

00:09.313 --> 00:11.924
<i>- In the criminal
justice system,</i>

00:11.968 --> 00:14.623
<i>sexually based offenses are
considered especially heinous.</i>

00:14.666 --> 00:17.234
<i>In New York City,
the dedicated detectives</i>

00:17.278 --> 00:19.280
<i>who investigate
these vicious felonies</i>

00:19.323 --> 00:20.716
<i>are members of an elite squad</i>

00:20.759 --> 00:22.848
<i>known as
the Special Victims Unit.</i>

00:22.892 --> 00:24.720
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:26.200 --> 00:28.724
- I really wish
you would consider

00:28.767 --> 00:30.117
getting out of that unit.

00:30.160 --> 00:32.336
- Come on, Mother.
Let's not tonight.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.338
- Do you think
this is healthy for you?

00:34.382 --> 00:36.384
- You were raped,
for God's sake.

00:38.777 --> 00:41.824
- If your mom were still alive,
how old would she be?

00:41.867 --> 00:45.958
- Uh, my mother, Serena,
would have been 77.

00:46.002 --> 00:47.525
- Wow.
- Yeah.

00:47.569 --> 00:49.875
- And you were already
a detective when she died?

00:49.919 --> 00:51.660
- I was.

00:51.703 --> 00:54.054
- Did she like
that you were a detective?

00:54.097 --> 00:57.231
- Well, it sounds like
you're being the detective now.

00:59.015 --> 01:01.191
- Do you miss her?
- Yeah.

01:02.410 --> 01:05.152
- 'Cause she was
a good mom like you.

01:05.195 --> 01:07.502
- Noah, you should know by now

01:07.545 --> 01:10.418
that no one's
as good a mom as I am.

01:10.461 --> 01:13.551
- Mom, not at school.
-

01:13.595 --> 01:15.118
- Love you.
- I love you.

01:15.162 --> 01:17.816
Have a good day.
Put your mask on.

01:20.863 --> 01:21.994
<i>♪</i>

01:26.086 --> 01:28.131
<i>Sorry I was late.
I--</i>

01:28.175 --> 01:29.524
so I'm walking Noah
to school...

01:29.567 --> 01:30.960
- Mm-hmm.

01:31.003 --> 01:33.310
- And out of the blue,
he asked me about my mother.

01:33.354 --> 01:34.877
- You went with short answer?

01:34.920 --> 01:36.357
- Yeah.
- Good.

01:36.400 --> 01:37.793
- So what is this
about a suspect?

01:37.836 --> 01:39.273
- He walked himself in.

01:39.316 --> 01:41.101
He hasn't confessed yet,
but he says

01:41.144 --> 01:43.146
he will only speak
to the captain.

01:43.190 --> 01:44.887
And heads up,
this guy's a charmer.

01:49.500 --> 01:52.677
- I'm guilty.
- Oh, my God, Nick.

01:52.721 --> 01:55.332
Whose idea was this?
- Mine.

01:55.376 --> 01:57.291
- What, you're captain now,
you don't like surprises?

01:57.334 --> 01:59.815
- I've never liked surprises.

01:59.858 --> 02:01.208
Hey.
- Hey.

02:01.251 --> 02:03.035
- What brings you to New York?

02:03.079 --> 02:05.777
- Work, a job I've been on
the last few years.

02:05.821 --> 02:07.170
A company called FORYM.
- Yeah.

02:07.214 --> 02:08.519
- I thought you were a PI.

02:08.563 --> 02:10.695
- No, I told you he went back
to grad school.

02:10.739 --> 02:13.045
- In genetics
and forensic science.

02:13.089 --> 02:14.525
We test DNA samples

02:14.569 --> 02:17.006
that used to be considered
too small or too degraded.

02:17.049 --> 02:18.268
- Solving cold cases.

02:18.312 --> 02:20.444
That seems like
a good fit for you.

02:20.488 --> 02:21.924
- Which means
we can work together again.

02:21.967 --> 02:25.232
Nick has an old SVU case
that he wants to reopen.

02:27.234 --> 02:30.715
- 1996,
Haley West is 15 years old.

02:30.759 --> 02:32.456
Raped and strangled
on prom night.

02:32.500 --> 02:34.502
- Hold on,
this was one of Cragen's.

02:34.545 --> 02:37.200
I remember--I remember him
talking about it.

02:37.244 --> 02:39.637
But is it cold?

02:39.681 --> 02:42.118
Didn't they catch
the--the boyfriend?

02:42.162 --> 02:43.815
- Ian Ridley, yes.

02:43.859 --> 02:46.296
He actually did confess,
and he's still doing time,

02:46.340 --> 02:49.299
but he recanted at sentencing,

02:49.343 --> 02:51.388
and the only DNA
found on Haley's body

02:51.432 --> 02:52.650
was from his saliva.

02:52.694 --> 02:54.522
I was approached
by a true crime writer

02:54.565 --> 02:56.001
looking into
wrongful convictions.

02:56.045 --> 02:58.047
He asked me if we could try
to salvage old DNA,

02:58.090 --> 03:00.136
so I'm coming to you.

03:00.180 --> 03:03.531
- Well, let's pull the files,
see if anything's there.

03:05.228 --> 03:07.143
- 654.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.580
West.
Haley West, right here.

03:14.759 --> 03:18.241
Wow, she's so young.
And a sweet face.

03:18.285 --> 03:20.504
- Haley's mother
never got over losing her.

03:20.548 --> 03:22.158
Ian's not the killer.

03:24.769 --> 03:28.251
Hm, Burton Lowe,
the writer, he's here.

03:30.732 --> 03:33.778
- Nick, I thought you said
this place was a dump.

03:33.822 --> 03:36.303
- Ah, well, they've
fixed it up since I left.

03:36.346 --> 03:38.435
Burton Lowe,
Detective Amanda Rollins.

03:38.479 --> 03:39.436
- How do you do?
- Hi.

03:39.480 --> 03:40.916
- Captain's waiting for us.

03:42.918 --> 03:44.876
- Captain,
Nick's writer is here.

03:51.143 --> 03:53.624
- Burton.
- Olivia.

03:55.365 --> 03:59.195
You haven't changed.
- Neither have you.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.632
And now that we've established

04:01.676 --> 04:04.026
that we're both liars...
-

04:04.069 --> 04:05.419
- Nick, you didn't tell me

04:05.462 --> 04:09.727
that your crime writer
was--was Burton Lowe.

04:09.771 --> 04:11.512
- Should I have?

04:11.555 --> 04:16.212
- Um, we are old friends.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.214
- From a lifetime ago.

04:18.258 --> 04:23.437
<i>♪</i>

04:26.483 --> 04:33.621
<i>♪</i>

04:45.850 --> 04:52.770
<i>♪</i>

05:09.918 --> 05:12.442
- My mother
was an English professor.

05:12.486 --> 05:16.011
When I was 16, I started
dating one of her students.

05:16.054 --> 05:17.447
He was a senior.

05:17.491 --> 05:21.233
He was 21 years old,
and he asked me to marry him.

05:21.277 --> 05:25.237
- Look at this.
Serena would be proud.

05:25.281 --> 05:26.978
- Well, if you recall,

05:27.022 --> 05:29.154
that wasn't
Serena's strong suit.

05:29.198 --> 05:31.766
- No, it wasn't, was it?

05:33.768 --> 05:36.640
Anyway, Haley West.
- Yeah.

05:36.684 --> 05:38.903
- Yes, of course.
Please have a seat.

05:38.947 --> 05:42.516
So I called
my former captain, Cragen,

05:42.559 --> 05:45.345
and he said
that the boyfriend...

05:45.388 --> 05:48.086
- Ian Ridley.
- Confessed within 48 hours.

05:48.130 --> 05:50.654
- He did, but he was 18,
concussed, traumatized--

05:50.698 --> 05:52.221
- Concussed?

05:52.264 --> 05:54.310
- His initial story was that he
and Haley were making out

05:54.354 --> 05:56.747
when an unknown assailant
knocked him out.

05:56.791 --> 05:59.184
When he came to,
Haley was gone.

05:59.228 --> 06:00.969
- And they found
her strangled, beaten body

06:01.012 --> 06:03.058
two hours later
in Fort Tyron Park.

06:03.101 --> 06:06.931
- My take, he was probably
so guilt-ridden

06:06.975 --> 06:08.846
about what happened.

06:08.890 --> 06:10.282
- He convinced himself
that he did it?

06:10.326 --> 06:11.719
- Mm-hmm.

06:11.762 --> 06:13.373
- How'd you
get involved, Burton?

06:13.416 --> 06:16.114
- Ian's mother wrote to me
before she died.

06:16.158 --> 06:18.465
I promised her
I'd do right by him.

06:18.508 --> 06:20.292
At his parole hearing,

06:20.336 --> 06:23.165
the board was ready to release
Ian if he showed contrition.

06:23.208 --> 06:27.517
When it was time for Ian
to apologize, he couldn't.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.998
25 years behind bars,

06:30.041 --> 06:31.956
two words away
from walking free,

06:32.000 --> 06:33.393
and instead he says,

06:33.436 --> 06:37.658
"I believe in two things,
the truth and miracles.

06:37.701 --> 06:40.443
I know the truth,
and I need a miracle."

06:40.487 --> 06:43.707
- New DNA technology
can be that miracle.

06:43.751 --> 06:46.014
If there's even 15 cells
from the original sample,

06:46.057 --> 06:48.495
my company can tease out
a genetic profile.

06:48.538 --> 06:50.453
- After 25 years?
- Oh, yeah.

06:50.497 --> 06:54.326
- I'll need to call Carisi.
That's our ADA.

06:54.370 --> 06:56.024
- Understood.

06:59.244 --> 07:00.507
<i>♪</i>

07:00.550 --> 07:01.899
<i>- Here you go.</i>

07:01.943 --> 07:03.771
I had to send my gnomes
deep into the crypt

07:03.814 --> 07:05.990
to get this out.
- I owe you, Melinda.

07:06.034 --> 07:08.906
- Once an SVU detective,
always an SVU detective.

07:08.950 --> 07:11.039
You're lucky
this wasn't tossed.

07:11.082 --> 07:12.736
You do know
this is a closed case.

07:12.780 --> 07:14.390
- Yeah, we know
that the saliva

07:14.434 --> 07:16.261
on Haley West
matched Ian Ridley.

07:16.305 --> 07:18.742
We're just--we're hoping there
might be some other samples.

07:18.786 --> 07:21.005
- Barely--there was a trace
of seminal fluid

07:21.049 --> 07:23.878
in the autopsy rape kit.
- And it was never tested?

07:23.921 --> 07:25.880
- The quantity
was too low in '96,

07:25.923 --> 07:28.448
and, as is stated here,
the suspect confessed.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.885
M.E. Rogers had no reason
to perform more testing.

07:30.928 --> 07:32.800
- But it's still viable?
- Maybe.

07:32.843 --> 07:35.150
The kit sat
in freezer purgatory

07:35.193 --> 07:36.847
this whole time.

07:36.891 --> 07:40.372
As DNA degrades,
it's much harder to analyze.

07:40.416 --> 07:43.506
- But with our new tech,
mixture deconvolution,

07:43.550 --> 07:44.986
KinSNP analysis--

07:45.029 --> 07:47.205
- You get a chance
to rebuild the genetic profile.

07:47.249 --> 07:49.033
Well, look at you, Dr. Amaro.

07:49.077 --> 07:50.426
- Doctor, no, not yet,

07:50.470 --> 07:53.516
but I am working on it,
biophysics.

07:53.560 --> 07:57.955
Yeah, it's good to see you.
And thank you for this.

08:02.569 --> 08:05.093
- Cognitive reenactment?

08:05.136 --> 08:07.443
How'd you get a judge
to sign off on this?

08:07.487 --> 08:08.357
- Oh, I didn't.

08:08.400 --> 08:09.750
I pulled a favor
from an ADA

08:09.793 --> 08:11.621
who used to be
one of my detectives.

08:11.665 --> 08:16.060
- An ADA, a geneticist...
Your ex-detectives go places.

08:16.104 --> 08:17.627
- Well, I wish they wouldn't,

08:17.671 --> 08:22.197
because, as my mother
used to say, everyone leaves.

08:22.240 --> 08:23.677
- Serena was a little dark.

08:23.720 --> 08:28.420
- You know, Burton,
if you needed help on a case,

08:28.464 --> 08:32.947
you could've just told Nick
you knew me or gotten in touch.

08:32.990 --> 08:34.383
- I guess I was afraid

08:34.426 --> 08:38.474
that you'd just say no
considering how we ended.

08:39.475 --> 08:44.088
- You know, my mother made me
write that letter to you

08:44.132 --> 08:46.438
to break off our engagement.

08:46.482 --> 08:50.312
She told me that you had
a real girlfriend in college.

08:50.355 --> 08:51.966
- I did not.

08:53.315 --> 08:56.623
I was in love with you.
I told her that.

08:56.666 --> 09:00.104
- But you disappeared.

09:00.148 --> 09:03.847
- Oh, I wanted
to write you, to see you.

09:03.891 --> 09:06.763
She told me if I even tried
to get in touch,

09:06.807 --> 09:10.071
she'd have me
immediately expelled.

09:12.856 --> 09:15.032
- Well, then she lied
to both of us.

09:17.948 --> 09:20.603
- To be continued.

09:20.647 --> 09:23.693
<i>♪</i>

09:23.737 --> 09:25.086
Hello, Ian.

09:25.129 --> 09:26.914
This is Captain Benson
of the SVU.

09:26.957 --> 09:28.176
- Hey.

09:28.219 --> 09:30.787
- Mr. Lowe got you
to reopen my case?

09:30.831 --> 09:33.834
- If the detectives on the case
missed anything back then,

09:33.877 --> 09:36.619
then I wanna find that out.

09:36.663 --> 09:39.753
- Okay, well, thank you.

09:39.796 --> 09:46.934
<i>♪</i>

09:52.156 --> 09:53.549
I know it's been,
like, 25 years,

09:53.593 --> 09:57.335
but I'm kind of--

09:57.379 --> 09:59.207
kind of freaked
to be back here.

09:59.250 --> 10:01.557
- That's--that's
completely normal, Ian.

10:01.601 --> 10:04.516
Returning--
returning to the scene

10:04.560 --> 10:09.565
can trigger memories, right?
And that's why we're here.

10:09.609 --> 10:12.829
So anything that comes

10:12.873 --> 10:17.442
to your mind, a sound,
a smell, that can be helpful.

10:17.486 --> 10:20.358
<i>♪</i>

10:20.402 --> 10:22.404
- All right, guys, guys,
he's not going anywhere.

10:22.447 --> 10:24.232
- Yeah, just give him a minute.

10:29.498 --> 10:30.934
- Prom night.

10:32.588 --> 10:37.201
Haley and I booked it out here
past the chaperones.

10:38.768 --> 10:40.596
I snuck a bottle of champagne.

10:42.032 --> 10:44.556
We just wanted to be--

10:44.600 --> 10:47.037
we just wanted
to be together alone, you know.

10:47.081 --> 10:50.475
- Okay, so what kind
of night was it?

10:52.086 --> 10:55.350
- Warm, pitch dark.

10:55.393 --> 10:58.092
These lights--
they weren't here back then.

10:58.135 --> 11:00.616
So I lit a cigarette.

11:02.574 --> 11:04.620
Haley looked so pretty
in the dark.

11:07.667 --> 11:11.366
Then we started kissing.

11:11.409 --> 11:12.846
- Okay.

11:12.889 --> 11:17.067
Kissing and then?

11:17.111 --> 11:20.680
- Well, then we went
under the bleachers

11:20.723 --> 11:25.380
to, you know, go further.

11:25.423 --> 11:29.253
- But you didn't get that far?
- No.

11:35.956 --> 11:37.871
Haley was leaning
against that post.

11:37.914 --> 11:42.353
I was kissing her.
I had my eyes closed and then--

11:44.138 --> 11:45.792
- Okay, Ian, your eyes
were closed.

11:45.835 --> 11:47.924
Did you hear anything?

11:47.968 --> 11:51.885
- Yeah,
footsteps on the gravel,

11:51.928 --> 11:54.235
then somebody bashing me
on the skull.

11:55.802 --> 11:58.543
I remember Haley screaming,
him dragging her,

11:58.587 --> 12:00.458
and then
it all just went black.

12:00.502 --> 12:02.330
- So you're there now.
You're there now.

12:02.373 --> 12:03.635
- My ears were ringing.

12:05.768 --> 12:07.639
There was blood everywhere.

12:08.989 --> 12:12.296
I saw her corsage
in the grass over there.

12:12.340 --> 12:14.298
- Do you remember
calling the cops?

12:14.342 --> 12:17.345
- My parents did that.
I ran home.

12:17.388 --> 12:20.217
They took me to St. Luke's.
I got 12 stitches.

12:20.261 --> 12:22.742
- And the cops
still thought you did it?

12:22.785 --> 12:26.310
- I was so messed up,
I thought maybe I did do it,

12:26.354 --> 12:28.356
but I didn't.
I swear I didn't.

12:29.966 --> 12:32.316
I loved Haley.

12:32.360 --> 12:35.363
My whole life ended
the night that she died.

12:37.104 --> 12:40.063
Haley.

12:40.107 --> 12:42.152
<i>♪</i>

12:42.196 --> 12:43.850
- It's okay.

12:43.893 --> 12:48.724
<i>♪</i>

12:51.945 --> 12:56.514
- He was 21 years old,
and he asked me to marry him,

12:56.558 --> 12:59.082
and I said yes

12:59.126 --> 13:01.998
because I wanted
to get away from my mother.

13:02.042 --> 13:05.828
- It's kind of interesting,
isn't it?

13:05.872 --> 13:09.179
Him showing up
in your life now?

13:09.223 --> 13:13.357
Stabler, Burton.
Something's going on.

13:13.401 --> 13:15.098
- Nothing's going on.

13:15.142 --> 13:17.971
I mean, Burton is
obsessed with his work.

13:18.014 --> 13:20.364
You realize
that his last podcast series--

13:20.408 --> 13:23.803
he got a man off death row.
- Yeah, I Googled him too.

13:23.846 --> 13:25.848
You also saw that he just
split up with his girlfriend?

13:25.892 --> 13:28.198
- Yeah, the French journalist.
I did see that.

13:28.242 --> 13:31.636
- And right after,
out of all the cold cases,

13:31.680 --> 13:33.464
he chooses one from SVU?

13:33.508 --> 13:36.076
- Because Ian Ridley
is innocent.

13:40.254 --> 13:42.952
- The rape kit sample
was corrupted,

13:42.996 --> 13:44.475
but we did find a tiny amount

13:44.519 --> 13:45.912
of seminal fluid
on her underwear,

13:45.955 --> 13:47.522
enough to tease out
a genetic profile.

13:47.565 --> 13:48.784
- And it's not Ian's.

13:48.828 --> 13:50.873
- No, no,
we excluded him right away.

13:50.917 --> 13:53.702
No hits in CODIS.
We're looking at RMNE.

13:53.745 --> 13:54.746
- So random man...

13:54.790 --> 13:55.965
Not excluded.

13:56.009 --> 13:57.837
- I know.
- Of course you do.

13:57.880 --> 13:59.534
Then you also know
that the DA's office

13:59.577 --> 14:01.231
is unlikely to exonerate Ian--

14:01.275 --> 14:03.059
- Without a viable suspect,
mm-hmm.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.582
- That's the downside of CODIS,

14:04.626 --> 14:06.019
just doesn't have
all the answers.

14:06.062 --> 14:08.064
- But now that we have
a genetic profile,

14:08.108 --> 14:09.849
FORYM can start a search
of multiple

14:09.892 --> 14:12.286
geological databases
and ancestry sites.

14:12.329 --> 14:14.505
- With any luck,
we find distant relatives,

14:14.549 --> 14:16.159
digital shoe leather.

14:16.203 --> 14:18.074
- So we start wide.
We bore in.

14:18.118 --> 14:19.771
I mean, it's all
new bells and whistles,

14:19.815 --> 14:23.123
but it's basically old school.
Work the tree.

14:24.733 --> 14:28.693
- So I'm getting out of here?
- One step at a time, Ian.

14:28.737 --> 14:30.739
The lab did find male DNA

14:30.782 --> 14:32.741
on Haley's body
that wasn't yours.

14:32.784 --> 14:33.873
- Whose was it?

14:33.916 --> 14:35.309
- Well, we don't know that yet,

14:35.352 --> 14:38.486
but someone
who uploaded their DNA

14:38.529 --> 14:40.270
to a genealogical website

14:40.314 --> 14:43.795
is a close relative,
either a brother or a cousin,

14:43.839 --> 14:46.537
and we've identified
three possible suspects.

14:46.581 --> 14:48.757
- One of the men lived
in California at the time,

14:48.800 --> 14:51.412
one in Ohio,
but one of the men was local.

14:51.455 --> 14:56.156
- In fact,
he worked at your high school.

14:56.199 --> 14:57.374
- Mr. Murray?

14:58.985 --> 15:01.161
I mean,
he was the girls' tennis coach,

15:01.204 --> 15:05.730
but there's no way he did this.
He loved Haley.

15:05.774 --> 15:08.908
<i>♪</i>

15:08.951 --> 15:10.866
- Well, like I told Liv,

15:10.910 --> 15:13.347
Roger Murray
was never a suspect.

15:13.390 --> 15:16.437
<i>I mean, how solid
is this new tech?</i>

15:16.480 --> 15:19.831
- It works, but we don't have
Murray's DNA yet.

15:19.875 --> 15:21.398
We do have a familial match.

15:21.442 --> 15:24.488
- Captain, you interviewed him
three times--why?

15:24.532 --> 15:27.796
- Well, he was one of the last
people to see her alive.

15:27.839 --> 15:30.842
He was a chaperone at the prom,
and he also said

15:30.886 --> 15:33.976
that he saw Haley
and Ian get in a fight.

15:34.020 --> 15:35.978
- Hm.
Yeah, what else did he say?

15:36.022 --> 15:38.894
<i>- Well, he said that Ian
was really weird,</i>

15:38.938 --> 15:41.375
<i>couldn't get a date
in his own grade,</i>

15:41.418 --> 15:44.465
<i>and that Haley
had confided in him</i>

