16:49.791 --> 16:51.923
- We're only here as NYPD.

16:51.967 --> 16:53.838
We're just trying
to give you some closure.

16:53.882 --> 16:55.318
- Closure?

16:55.362 --> 16:57.538
My husband
and daughter are dead.

16:57.581 --> 17:00.106
I'll never see Haley
walk down the aisle.

17:00.149 --> 17:03.239
I'll never bake cookies
for my grandchildren.

17:03.283 --> 17:05.415
- And we can't change
what happened to Haley.

17:05.459 --> 17:09.028
- Hey, leave me alone.
Ian confessed.

17:09.071 --> 17:11.769
And Roger sends me a card
every year

17:11.813 --> 17:13.771
on the anniversary of her death

17:13.815 --> 17:16.774
just to let me know...

17:16.818 --> 17:19.734
I'm not mourning alone.

17:19.777 --> 17:24.173
<i>♪</i>

17:24.217 --> 17:26.741
- Excuse me, Mr. Murray.
- Can I help you?

17:26.784 --> 17:28.482
- Yeah,
I'm ADA Dominic Carisi.

17:28.525 --> 17:31.615
I was wondering if we could
talk to you about Haley West.

17:31.659 --> 17:34.444
- Yeah, her mother told me that
you guys were nosing around.

17:34.488 --> 17:36.794
Look, I told everything
I knew to the police.

17:36.838 --> 17:38.100
It was Ian Ridley.

17:38.144 --> 17:40.711
- Yeah, we know.
I'm Nick Amaro.

17:40.755 --> 17:42.278
Yeah, my old captain, Cragen,

17:42.322 --> 17:44.106
told me he appreciated
all your help back then.

17:44.150 --> 17:45.499
That's why we're here.

17:45.542 --> 17:47.849
- I don't understand,
Ian's in prison.

17:47.892 --> 17:49.111
- Oh, he is,

17:49.155 --> 17:51.113
but, you know,
he's trying for an appeal.

17:51.157 --> 17:53.115
- Yeah, he's trying to get
the DNA re-examined.

17:53.159 --> 17:55.422
- Unbelievable.
- Yeah, tell us about it.

17:55.465 --> 17:57.337
Look, as a precaution,
we're gathering samples

17:57.380 --> 18:00.035
from anyone Hailey
interacted with that night,

18:00.079 --> 18:02.081
and Haley's mom
told us you chaperoned.

18:02.124 --> 18:05.649
- Yeah, I chaperoned, but--
- What's going on?

18:05.693 --> 18:07.086
- How you doing, ma'am?

18:07.129 --> 18:08.652
I'm Dominic Carisi.
I'm with the DA's office.

18:08.696 --> 18:10.524
- Ian Ridley
is trying to reopen the case.

18:10.567 --> 18:12.134
I mean,
it's a bunch of nonsense--

18:12.178 --> 18:14.267
- Which is why
we need your husband's help.

18:14.310 --> 18:16.486
We know how much Haley
meant to him.

18:17.705 --> 18:19.881
- Roger, do whatever they ask.

18:28.368 --> 18:30.413
- Haley was beautiful
that night.

18:30.457 --> 18:32.763
- Her mother said that she was
like a daughter to you.

18:32.807 --> 18:36.071
- I loved that girl,
and I would never hurt her.

18:36.115 --> 18:38.160
She knew that.
- I'm sure she did, Mr. Murray.

18:38.204 --> 18:40.119
- You looked out for her.
You protected her.

18:40.162 --> 18:41.381
- That was all
I ever tried to do.

18:41.424 --> 18:44.427
- At the night of the prom?
-

18:44.471 --> 18:46.037
I let her down.

18:46.081 --> 18:48.170
I mean, I saw Ian
dragging her out.

18:48.214 --> 18:49.693
I should've stopped him.

18:49.737 --> 18:51.086
- You should have, or you did?

18:52.218 --> 18:53.828
- Well, that was
a long time ago.

18:53.871 --> 18:56.396
Uh, whatever I said back then,
that was the truth.

18:56.439 --> 18:59.399
- The thing is, Mr. Murray,
with this new DNA technology,

18:59.442 --> 19:02.489
it picks up the tiniest amount.

19:02.532 --> 19:05.100
Like, even if you were
to have touched her corsage...

19:05.144 --> 19:07.189
<i>♪</i>

19:07.233 --> 19:08.799
- Yeah,
and I might've done that.

19:08.843 --> 19:10.366
- Okay, that's helpful.

19:10.410 --> 19:12.194
- Yeah, and now
that I think about it, I did.

19:12.238 --> 19:14.283
I touched her arm because I
pulled her away from him.

19:14.327 --> 19:16.024
- Well, was that at the dance
or on the field?

19:16.067 --> 19:18.200
Just in case we find
your DNA on her corsage.

19:18.244 --> 19:20.724
They found that at the field.

19:20.768 --> 19:22.726
- What, and they kept that?

19:22.770 --> 19:25.076
<i>♪</i>

19:25.120 --> 19:27.122
No, I really don't remember,

19:27.166 --> 19:30.995
but it--it might've been
after the--afterwards, sure.

19:31.039 --> 19:32.432
- So you did follow them.
It makes sense.

19:32.475 --> 19:35.522
You were worried about her.
- Haley gave me a look.

19:35.565 --> 19:37.393
She was afraid of Ian,

19:37.437 --> 19:39.613
and she wanted me
to protect her.

19:39.656 --> 19:41.092
- Which you always did.

19:41.136 --> 19:42.355
- Yeah,
and I was the only one.

19:42.398 --> 19:45.096
I'm--no dad,
her mom overwhelmed,

19:45.140 --> 19:47.447
and that Ian, he was a bad kid.

19:47.490 --> 19:48.970
- So you had
to follow her and Ian?

19:49.013 --> 19:50.363
- Yeah, and he
was all over her.

19:50.406 --> 19:55.194
Hand on her--her breast.
His mouth everywhere.

19:55.237 --> 19:57.500
- You had to stop that
for Haley.

19:57.544 --> 19:59.154
- Who knows
what he might've done?

19:59.198 --> 20:02.636
So, yeah, I stopped that.
I stopped that good.

20:04.159 --> 20:06.161
- How'd you stop Ian,
Mr. Murray?

20:06.205 --> 20:08.990
- 'Cause we know Ian
was hit on the head.

20:09.033 --> 20:10.948
They found
a bottle at the scene.

20:10.992 --> 20:13.212
- Yeah, it's champagne

20:13.255 --> 20:15.779
because the--the kid
brought it himself.

20:15.823 --> 20:17.607
She was only 15.

20:17.651 --> 20:20.088
- So you had to step in
for Haley.

20:22.395 --> 20:23.744
- I really don't remember,

20:23.787 --> 20:28.488
and I'm gonna need my digitalis
and a lawyer.

20:28.531 --> 20:35.451
<i>♪</i>

20:36.496 --> 20:38.802
- All these years
lying to himself.

20:38.846 --> 20:42.023
he was aroused.
She screamed.

20:42.066 --> 20:43.981
He put his hand over her mouth.

20:44.025 --> 20:47.768
- Okay.
- Sorry, my writer's head.

20:47.811 --> 20:51.206
I'll tell Ian.

20:51.250 --> 20:55.950
- Oh, let's wait for the DNA.
- Oh, right, right.

20:55.993 --> 21:00.171
Wow, Olivia,
how do you do this?

21:00.215 --> 21:03.740
- It's a lot, you know,

21:03.784 --> 21:06.482
but I spend time with my son.

21:06.526 --> 21:10.312
I listen to music.
I go on walks when I can.

21:10.356 --> 21:13.663
- How about a walk now?
I could use one.

21:14.882 --> 21:16.579
- Give me a minute.

21:16.623 --> 21:19.495
- New York,
still my favorite city.

21:19.539 --> 21:21.410
- Not Paris?

21:21.454 --> 21:24.283
Didn't you live there
with your girlfriend?

21:24.326 --> 21:26.110
- Ex.
- Oh.

21:26.154 --> 21:29.026
- She may have ruined
that city for me.

21:29.070 --> 21:30.941
An old man dating a young woman

21:30.985 --> 21:32.421
always ends up
playing the fool.

21:32.465 --> 21:36.120
Have you been to France?
- I have, Paris once.

21:36.164 --> 21:39.515
- Romantic trip?
- It was, actually.

21:39.559 --> 21:43.171
- Oh, is he
still in the picture?

21:43.214 --> 21:44.738
- He's not.

21:46.392 --> 21:48.829
- Well, here's my hotel.

21:48.872 --> 21:50.700
- Plaza?

21:50.744 --> 21:53.399
- Podcasting has been
very good to me.

21:54.835 --> 21:56.445
You have time for a nightcap?

21:57.359 --> 22:00.101
- I could be persuaded.

22:10.285 --> 22:13.288
- Uh, I'm sorry.

22:14.245 --> 22:18.902
That wasn't very gentlemanly.

22:18.946 --> 22:21.165
- I didn't mind.

22:31.437 --> 22:33.134
- When a father is absent,

22:33.177 --> 22:34.962
it is not unusual
for a younger girl

22:35.005 --> 22:37.834
to be attracted
to an older man.

22:37.878 --> 22:39.401
- That's what this is about?

22:40.837 --> 22:43.187
- It happens a lot more
than you think.

22:43.231 --> 22:44.798
- How old were you?

22:46.930 --> 22:49.672
- Almost 17.
- And he was?

22:49.716 --> 22:51.805
- Older than 17.

22:54.198 --> 22:56.462
- Hey, beautiful.
Midnight snack?

22:56.505 --> 22:58.855
-
- Raided the minibar.

23:04.383 --> 23:05.471
What you thinking about?

23:07.821 --> 23:11.259
- I'm just time-traveling.

23:11.302 --> 23:13.827
- Can you believe?

23:13.870 --> 23:15.916
All those years,

23:15.959 --> 23:17.613
and it didn't matter.

23:17.657 --> 23:21.269
-
They added up.

23:21.312 --> 23:23.880
- Well, in certain places.

23:25.316 --> 23:26.274
- Do you know
what I think about

23:26.317 --> 23:28.189
when I think of you?
- What?

23:29.364 --> 23:32.628
- Us cycling
through Central Park,

23:32.672 --> 23:36.153
picnicking on the Great Lawn
as night falls

23:36.197 --> 23:38.199
and the city lights
surround us.

23:38.242 --> 23:41.332
-
- What?

23:43.160 --> 23:44.771
- That was a sweet night.

23:46.990 --> 23:49.210
- So is this.

23:51.604 --> 23:54.433
- Oh, I'm sorry.

23:54.476 --> 23:56.826
That could be my nanny.

23:59.002 --> 24:01.570
No, it's a text from Amaro.

24:01.614 --> 24:04.704
"Good news.
The semen sample came back

24:04.747 --> 24:06.445
"from Haley's underwear,

24:06.488 --> 24:09.535
and it is a match
to Roger Murray."

24:12.538 --> 24:14.975
I don't even know
how to respond to that.

24:18.587 --> 24:20.328
Mm.

24:20.371 --> 24:22.504
And it is my sitter.

24:22.548 --> 24:24.898
I'm sorry.
I gotta go.

24:26.334 --> 24:29.859
Listen, I will--
I will call Carisi,

24:29.903 --> 24:32.601
and I will push him
to get Ian released.

24:32.645 --> 24:34.385
- Okay, he needs a lawyer.

24:35.604 --> 24:38.738
- And I know
exactly who to call.

24:38.781 --> 24:41.044
- My client
was completely absolved

24:41.088 --> 24:42.655
by the DNA evidence.

24:42.698 --> 24:47.094
He spent 25 years in prison
for a crime he didn't commit.

24:47.137 --> 24:49.531
What possible reason
could there be for a delay?

24:49.575 --> 24:51.446
- The DA's office
is supportive.

24:51.490 --> 24:53.361
We've agreed to release
Mr. Ridley from prison.

24:53.404 --> 24:55.363
- But you haven't vacated
the conviction.

24:55.406 --> 24:56.625
- You said Roger killed her.

24:56.669 --> 24:57.931
He should pay
for what he did to Haley.

24:57.974 --> 24:59.149
- Yes, he should.

24:59.193 --> 25:00.499
- We all want justice,
but I can't

25:00.542 --> 25:02.370
just declare Murray guilty
without due process.

25:02.413 --> 25:04.067
- You did it to Ian
25 years ago.

25:04.111 --> 25:06.200
- Burton, please.

25:06.243 --> 25:08.681
- Look, I'll ask
the judge to expedite,

25:08.724 --> 25:10.552
but I'm gonna need
to start prepping my witnesses.

25:10.596 --> 25:12.162
- I'm happy to testify.

25:12.206 --> 25:13.816
- My expert witnesses.

25:16.340 --> 25:17.603
Where's Amaro?

25:19.082 --> 25:20.431
- Well, thank you, counselor.

25:20.475 --> 25:22.216
Before I put Ian in the car,
he told me

25:22.259 --> 25:24.740
he feels safe in your hands.

25:24.784 --> 25:27.351
I just wish he'd had
a real lawyer the first time.

25:27.395 --> 25:29.353
It's gonna be
an adjustment for him.

25:29.397 --> 25:31.486
- He knows that.

25:31.530 --> 25:33.270
Excuse me.
Showtime.

25:33.314 --> 25:34.576
- We get it.

25:34.620 --> 25:36.926
- I do have
a podcast to promote.

25:41.757 --> 25:44.934
- Two words of advice.
Watch yourself.

25:44.978 --> 25:47.241
I used to have
clients in publishing.

25:47.284 --> 25:49.330
He's got a reputation.

25:49.373 --> 25:52.289
So just... eyes open.

25:53.421 --> 25:54.901
- Always.

25:59.906 --> 26:02.865
Captain. <i>
- Liv, I'm glad I caught you.</i>

26:02.909 --> 26:04.606
<i>I've been thinking
about Roger Murray.</i>

26:04.650 --> 26:07.087
- Yeah, he's fighting
the DNA evidence.

26:07.130 --> 26:09.219
<i>- That's why I'm calling.</i>

26:09.263 --> 26:13.180
<i>He always felt so guilty about
letting down Haley's mother.</i>

26:13.223 --> 26:15.878
<i>Make sure that she is
at that hearing tomorrow.</i>

26:15.922 --> 26:19.273
- We'll do, Captain.
Thank you.

26:19.316 --> 26:22.798
<i>- Well, thank you, Captain.</i>

26:24.583 --> 26:27.542
<i>You don't know how proud
it makes me to say that.</i>

26:30.545 --> 26:32.373
<i>♪</i>

26:33.592 --> 26:36.116
<i>♪</i>

26:36.159 --> 26:39.075
- Our company's Brooklyn lab
has New York State Department

26:39.119 --> 26:42.122
of Health approval to perform
forensic DNA testing.

26:42.165 --> 26:43.689
- Thank you, Mr. Amaro.

26:43.732 --> 26:45.560
And here is that certification,
Your Honor.

26:45.604 --> 26:47.823
- Thank you, Counselor Carisi.

26:47.867 --> 26:51.435
- Your Honor, again,
my client is a retired teacher

26:51.479 --> 26:52.959
who spends Saturdays coaching

26:53.002 --> 26:54.787
his granddaughter's
softball team

26:54.830 --> 26:57.093
on a field
that's been named after him.

26:57.137 --> 26:58.529
He still gets holiday cards

26:58.573 --> 27:00.662
from kids he taught
three decades ago.

27:00.706 --> 27:02.664
- We're not addressing
any of that at this hearing.

27:02.708 --> 27:04.797
The people
have presented their case.

27:04.840 --> 27:08.322
- Frankly, Your Honor, I worry
that the ADA and this court

27:08.365 --> 27:09.976
are being used to publicize

27:10.019 --> 27:12.326
this DNA company
before it goes public.

27:12.369 --> 27:14.371
- Enough, Mr. Roth.

27:14.415 --> 27:15.808
I've heard your arguments,

27:15.851 --> 27:17.505
and I've heard
this state's case.

27:17.548 --> 27:19.550
I'm ruling
in favor of the state.

27:19.594 --> 27:21.944
The DNA will be admissible
at trial.

27:21.988 --> 27:23.816
- Thank you, Your Honor.

27:23.859 --> 27:28.908
- I need to change my plea.
I want to change my plea.

27:28.951 --> 27:31.606
- Not the time.
Not the place, Mr. Murray.

27:31.650 --> 27:32.825
- Mr. Murray,
we can talk about this.

27:32.868 --> 27:35.305
- No, I don't wanna talk
about it anymore.

27:35.349 --> 27:37.177
<i>♪</i>

27:37.220 --> 27:39.179
I killed that poor girl.

27:39.222 --> 27:44.314
<i>♪</i>

27:44.358 --> 27:47.404
I'm sorry, Joyce.

27:48.928 --> 27:52.018
I've--I've never
forgiven myself.

27:52.061 --> 27:59.025
<i>♪</i>

28:09.339 --> 28:10.993
- So is it over?

28:11.037 --> 28:12.734
- The judge will want Murray
to allocute,

28:12.778 --> 28:13.779
make sure that the guilty plea

28:13.822 --> 28:15.258
was knowing
and voluntary, but--

28:15.302 --> 28:17.130
- So, soon?

28:17.173 --> 28:19.741
- I'll speak to the DA,
insist it's time.

28:19.785 --> 28:22.483
-
- Congratulations.

28:22.526 --> 28:24.528
- To both of us.

28:24.572 --> 28:27.531
I'm gonna call Ian,
and then dinner?

28:27.575 --> 28:30.360
- That sounds great.
- Excuse me.

28:30.404 --> 28:32.188
You're a Captain Benson,
the head of SVU?

28:32.232 --> 28:33.320
- I am.

28:33.363 --> 28:34.756
- Can I ask you
what you're doing

28:34.800 --> 28:37.628
working with a predator?
- I'm sorry?

28:37.672 --> 28:40.370
- Whoa, what's going on?

28:40.414 --> 28:41.937
- You don't
remember me, Burton?

28:41.981 --> 28:43.156
Andrea Malone.

28:43.199 --> 28:44.984
- Yes, of course.
I remember you, Andrea.

28:45.027 --> 28:46.768
You were
my editor's intern on--

28:46.812 --> 28:49.423
- On your last novel
10 years ago.

28:49.466 --> 28:51.251
Ask him what he did
to me back then.

28:51.294 --> 28:53.035
I was only 20 years old.

28:54.602 --> 28:56.735
- Andrea, if I've upset you
in some way,

28:56.778 --> 28:58.606
